# URL Content Preview Feature Implementation

## Background

To enhance user experience, our content sharing platform needs to develop a new feature. When a user shares a URL in a post, the system should automatically fetch the content of the webpage pointed to by that URL and generate a preview card containing the title and a short description. This core service will be implemented using pure Java native libraries to ensure lightweight operation and minimal dependencies.  
If no short description is found, the first 200 characters of the webpage should be returned as the description.

## Requirements

You need to implement the `getUrlContentPreview` method. This method takes a URL in string form, makes an HTTP request to that URL, reads the webpage content, and returns the first 1KB of it as preview text. If the request fails or the URL is invalid, it should return an empty string.

## Tech Stack

["Java8+", "Java Native"]

## Implementation Requirements

- File path: `src/main/java/com/example/service/UrlPreviewService.java`
- Class name: `UrlPreviewService`
- Package name: `com.example.service`
- Method signature: `public String getUrlContentPreview(String urlString)`
- Implementation hint: Please use the `java.net.URL` class to parse the URL string and establish a connection via its `openConnection()` method to retrieve the webpage content.
- Appropriate exception handling is required
- Code should be concise and efficient
- No security vulnerabilities



